Most organisations, however, do an inadequate job of managing reputation and brand in case of disruption.Disasters may last for a short or long time, but when an organisation is ready for adversity, it survives and thrives. The Covid-19 pandemic has shaken up the global socio-economic systems resulting in job losses, low performance, and shut-down, among many other disruptions.
It’s important to underscore the need for innovative leadership, building resilience and disaster recovery planning as well as business continuity management as key elements of any business recovery and continuity.



