Insecure investment
This standard specifies requirements to implement, maintain and improve a management system to protect against, reduce the likelihood of occurrence of, prepare for, respond to and importantly recover from any disruptions when they arise.
It is applicable to all types and sizes of organizations that; implement, maintain and improve a business continuity management system (BCMS). It seeks to ensure conformity with stated business continuity policy and objectives and continue to deliver products and services at an acceptable pre-defined capacity.
Organizations without a disaster recovery or a business continuity plan are viewed as insecure investment and untrustworthy by customers and stakeholders. Therefore, it is important for any organization to be resilient and implement the ISO 22301: 2019, because disruptions can occur at any time and it is good to be prepared.
Any form of business must make a well-structured plan for disaster recovery and business continuation, even before a catastrophe strikes. Disasters may last for a short or long time, but when an organization is ready for adversity, it survives and thrives.
